<br />

<br />
There is enough brain power to maintain all of her bodily functions and enough cognitive power to concentrate on the moving baloon. That doesn't sound brain dead to me.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Some basic brain anatomy at a simplistic level. The brain can be split into two parts;
<br />
The modern brain which controls , speech , awareness, reasoning...
<br />
The ancient brain, aka the brain stem, which contrs the autonomous nervous system, breathing, heart beat etc. 
<br />

<br />
I haven't seen the video but there are cases of tracking where the visual cortex remains intact or partly intact and tracks moving object. The cat scan supports that.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Badmorda wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">A long time ago, the husband denied her any sort of therapy. Denied the family any sort of visits. These are not the actions of someone who cares...</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
I'm not judging the husband, as coming from a paramedical background, I understand the absolute horror of seeing someone who you love lying in a vegatitive state. That is in simplistic terms you've seen your loved one going from a warm loving human being to a dried out husk.
<br />

<br />
I also understand and support the desire to let this unrecoverable person die with dignity.
<br />

<br />
Letting someone starve with appropriate use of morphine to allay the symptoms is not inhumane. 
<br />

<br />
Of course if we could get over this primeval instinct to keep fighting for life where it has long since fled we would allow here to die with a humane lethal overdose.
<br />

<br />
It is a shame that the family differs and has caused this poor man untold grief by fighting him in public and the courts but in the end it is is decision as guardian to make.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=99350" target="_blank" class="postlink">Wolj</a>
