<br />

<br />
From everything I've seen/read in the last week or two, she is brain-dead, she has no cognitive skills, no thought process and no ability to act beyond reactions. Just because her body is still functioning doesnt mean her brain is. Almost everything that she is "capable" of are reflex reactions or abilites that most non-sentient life forms can do.
<br />

<br />
I think you need to seperate brain functionality (reasoning, thought, speech, etc) from reactionary impulses (turning towards bright light, turning towards sound, facial expressions due to stimuli). Even a plant can accomplish those last few, and they have no brain to speak of. 
<br />

<br />
What is left of that woman is long since gone. Her parents are just keeping her body alive, the rest is dead.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=345799" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://cs.franklin.edu/~kubasa01/Kessig3.gif" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
